dcterms:description: Medline is the US National Library of Medical/Biomedical dataset containing millions of biomedical scientific documents, built around the MeSH thesaurus, which contains about 30,000 MeSH descriptors used for semantic indexing.
dcterms:title: Medline

dcterms:description: LitCovid is a subset of the Medline database focused on COVID-19 literature, containing articles extracted via PubMed using specific keywords related to the coronavirus, with its own categorization of articles.
dcterms:title: LitCovid
